claim.claim-text:
1. Apparatus for determining the clearance between a member and a casing surface over and relative to which the member moves, comprising:
a main waveguide, the waveguide having a proximal end and a distal end, the distal end being adjacent the casing surface and the proximal end being at a position recessed in the casing;
a transmitter/receiver, provided at the proximal end of the main waveguide, and
a reference element at a position intermediate the proximal and distal ends of the waveguide or at the distal end of the waveguide;
wherein the transmitter receiver is arranged to transmit an electromagnetic signal through the main waveguide and receive:
(i) a first portion of the electromagnetic signal reflected from the reference element;
(ii) a second portion of the electromagnetic signal reflected from the casing surface, and
(iii) a third portion of the electromagnetic signal reflected from the member.
